{"search_data": "Central, JharkhandJharkhand Govt. Distributed 20,051 Pucca Houses Under PMAY to Homeless People \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u0902Jharkhand PM Awas YojanaThese 20,051 houses have been constructed with a plinth area of 30 sqm for each beneficiary. The PMAY houses are being designed and constructed with all basic residential amenities. The house will have two rooms, a kitchen and a toilet. The construction cost of house is around Rs. 3.57 lakh.Out of total cost of house, the state government will provide Rs. 75,000 while Rs. 1,50,000 would be provided by the Central government. Rest of the amount which is Rs. 1.33 lakh would have to be paid the bye beneficiary itself. In addition, within a month, all the houses under the scheme will get power and water connection while BPL households would get LPG connection too.The state government has also announced 41 cities open defection free (ODF) across the state.Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY)PMAY is an centrally sponsored housing scheme which was launched in 2015 by the Prime Minister Shri Narendra Modi. The Ministry of Housing and Urban Poverty Alleviation is operating and formulating all the procedures regarding the implementation of housing scheme in urban areas. The list of PMAY beneficiaries is being prepared from the SECC-2011 data based on several factors including income of the household.The objective of the scheme is to provide affordable and eco \u2013 friendly houses to all the homeless citizens by the year of 2022.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}